          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Foreign Business Bribery Prohibition Act of 2016</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Foreign Corrupt Practices Act of 1977 (FCPA) to authorize private rights of action against persons that violate the FCPA's anti-bribery provisions, which prohibit giving things of value to foreign officials or political parties for purposes of obtaining or retaining business. A person that violates the FCPA's anti-bribery provisions shall be liable for up to treble damages to a securities issuer, domestic business concern, or U.S. person damaged by the violation. </p> <p>A plaintiff must prove an FCPA anti-bribery violation by the defendant that: (1) prevented the plaintiff from obtaining or retaining business, and (2) assisted the defendant in obtaining or retaining such business.</p>]]></text>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2016-08-01T21:39:59Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
